ranked_diseases.explanation: All three reference cases with identical phenotypes (chronic kidney disease and proteinuria) were diagnosed with this condition. The patient's presentation matches perfectly with the reference cases.
Another subtype of autosomal dominant tubulointerstitial kidney disease that presents with similar features of chronic kidney disease and proteinuria.
Additional subtype of ADTKD presenting with chronic kidney disease and proteinuria, though less common than types 1 and 2.
Another ADTKD subtype with similar presentation but rarer occurrence compared to earlier subtypes.
Fifth subtype of ADTKD that can present with chronic kidney disease and proteinuria.
Common cause of proteinuria and chronic kidney disease in adults, though reference cases suggest tubulointerstitial disease is more likely.
Common glomerular disease causing proteinuria and progressive chronic kidney disease, though typically also presents with hematuria which is not mentioned here.
Hereditary nephritis that can present with proteinuria and progressive kidney disease, though usually has additional features like hearing loss.
